server {
    listen 80;
    location / {
        root /usr/share/nginx/html;
        try_files $uri /index.html;
    }
}
```

Then in Railway:
1. Click **"New Service"** → connect same GitHub repo
2. Set **Root Directory** to `frontend`
3. Set env var: `REACT_APP_API_URL=https://rubber-shoe-backend.railway.app`

---

### Option B — Backend Serves the Frontend (Single Service)

Spring Boot serves the built React files as static assets. **One URL for everything.**
```
https://rubber-shoe-pos.railway.app/          → React app
https://rubber-shoe-pos.railway.app/api/...   → Spring Boot API
